Currently, if the user would like to associate a project with a certain scheme, they would have to do it manually via the Project administration page. However, if the user wants to edit multiple projects, then they would have to perform it one-by-one.

It would be useful if the user could bulk associate multiple projects with a certain scheme. For example, notification scheme, permission scheme, etc. This would especially help users with a high number of projects, especially when they would like to clear outdated schemes.

h3. Steps to reproduce:
- Set up a JIRA instance with [Atlassian Developer Toolbox|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.atlassian.devrel.developer-toolbox-plugin] (current version: 2.0.3);
- Create a test project and an issue (FOOBAR-1);
- Browse to _Administration -> Developer Toolbox -> Developer Toolbox -> REST API Browser_.
- Click in _Applinks Product Plugin_ and select _Atlassian JIRA - Plugins - REST Plugin_ which has the URL http://$BASE_URL/rest/api/2;
- Scroll down the screen and look for the *GET* method which belongs to the */issue/\{issueIdOrKey\}/transitions* method;
- Enter "FOOBAR-1" on the _issueIdOrKey_ parameter and click in _Execute_;
- Pick a transition ID and at random;
- Now scroll down the screen a little bit and look for the *POST* method which belongs to */issue/\{issueIdOrKey\}/transitions*;
- Enter "FOOBAR-1" on the _issueIdOrKey_ parameter, add the following parameters on the request field and click in _Execute_:
{code}
{
"update": {
"comment": [
{
"add": {
"body": "resolving issue"
}
}
]
},
"transition":
{ "id": "5" }
}
{code}

